{{short description|2018 book}} {{Infobox book | name = An Elephant in my Kitchen | image = An Elephant in my Kitchen.jpg | author = Francoise Malby-Anthony with Katja Willemsen | language = English | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[Pan Macmillan]] (London) | pub_date = 2018 | pages = 324 pp. | isbn = 978-1-5098-6491-1 }}
'''''An Elephant in my Kitchen''''', published in July 2018 by [[Pan Macmillan]] in London, is the first book written by South African author and conservationist Francoise Malby-Anthony-Anthony along with author Katja Willemsen.<ref>{{cite web |title=An Elephant In My Kitchen: Without water, life stops |url=https://www.news24.com/Books/an-elephant-in-my-kitchen-without-water-life-stops-20180820 |website=News24 |accessdate=11 October 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=An Elephant in My Kitchen – Francoise Malby Anthony |url=http://www.polity.org.za/article/an-elephant-in-my-kitchen-francoise-malby-anthony-2018-08-30 |website=Polity.org.za |accessdate=11 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Françoise Malby-Anthony shares lessons learnt from 'An Elephant In My Kitchen' |url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sunday-times/opinion-and-analysis/2018-08-18-franoise-malby-anthony-shares-lessons-learnt-from-an-elephant-in-my-kitchen/ |accessdate=11 October 2018}}</ref>
The story is told out of the eyes of Francoise Malby-Anthony who continued to manage [[Thula Thula]] Private Game Reserve in [[KwaZulu Natal]] [[South Africa]] after [[Lawrence Anthony]]'s death in 2012, and is considered the [[sequel]] of [[The Elephant Whisperer]] published by [[Lawrence Anthony]] in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |title=Talking Books Ep 25: ‘An Elephant in My Kitchen’ book by Francoise Malby-Anthony - CNBC Africa |url=https://www.cnbcafrica.com/videos/2018/09/05/talking-books-ep-25-an-elephant-in-my-kitchen-book-by-francoise-malby-anthony/ |website=CNBC Africa |accessdate=11 October 2018 |date=5 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=‘An Elephant in My Kitchen’ a must-read for wildlife lovers |url=https://www.heraldlive.co.za/lifestyle/leisure/2018-09-03-an-elephant-in-my-kitchen-a-must-read-for-wildlife-lovers/ |accessdate=11 October 2018}}</ref>
The book has been the number one bestseller in [[South Africa]] for a number of weeks in 2018,{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} and has been launched in the [[UK]], [[Australia]], [[New Zealand]] and [[India]]. The book is launched in [[Canada]] and the [[United States]] in November 2018.
