'''Transit 5E-1''', [[International Designator]] 1963-038C, is an [[artificial satellite]] of the [[United States Department of Defense]] and launched in September 28, 1963, aboard a [[Thor (rocket family)|Thor]] rocket from the [[Vandenberg Air Force Base]].

==Launch==
Transit 5E-1 was launched for studying charged particles, [[magnetic field]]s and [[solar spectra]], as well as doing [[geodesy|geodetic]] research.{{Citation needed|date=May 2011}}

It was launched to a [[polar orbit]], from where it did geomagnetic and geodetic measurements. Electrical power was produced by four [[solar panel]]s. After August 1969, the satellite did measurements infrequently. The last data were transmitted in November, 1974.

