{{Infobox ecoregion | name = Zacatonal | image = Nevado de toluca a.JPG | image_size = 250 | image_alt = | image_caption = Zacatonal at the [[Nevado de Toluca]] | country = [[Mexico]] | country1 = <!--[[Guatemala]]--><!--Needs a reliable source--> | bird_species = 204 | mammal_species = 48 | plant_species = | habitat_loss = | habitat_loss_ref = | protected = | protected_ref = | area = 306 | conservation = Relatively Stable/Intact<ref name=WWF>{{WWF ecoregion|id=nt1009|name=Zacatonal|accessdate=2013-08-24}}</ref> | biome = [[Montane grasslands and shrublands]] | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | global200 = }}
The '''Zacatonal''' is a [[montane grasslands and shrublands|montane grassland and shrubland]] [[ecoregion]] of central [[Mexico]],<ref name=WWF/> and Guatemala{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}.
==Description== The Zacatonal consists of several enclaves of grassland and shrubland occupying the highest peaks of the [[Trans-Mexican Volcanic Belt]], covering about {{convert|306|km2|sqmi|sp=us}}.
They are surrounded by the [[Trans-Mexican Volcanic Belt pine-oak forests]] ecoregion at lower elevations.
